# =============================================================================
# Soliplex Environment Variables Example
# =============================================================================
# Most soliplex configuration should be done in the 'installation.yaml'
# file (see https://soliplex.github.io/soliplex/config/filesystem_layout/).
#
# This example '.env' file exists to demonstrate configuring the handful
# of values which you might choose not to keep checked into your VCS.
#
# Copy this file to .env and configure with your actual values
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # Edit .env with your values
#   source .env  # On Unix/Linux/Mac
#   # Or configure in docker-compose.yaml or your deployment system
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# Installation environment variables
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ollama Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Use this value ONLY IF your 'installation.yaml file declares its own
# 'OLLAMA_BASE_URL' environment variable without any value.  Not that the
# URL to your Ollama server must *not* contain the '/v1' suffix.
#
# For local Ollama:
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
#
# For Docker containers accessing host:
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434
#
# For remote Ollama:
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://your-ollama-server:11434

# =============================================================================
# Installation Secrets
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# URL-safe token generation
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secret key for generating and validating MCP room tokens
# If not set, a random value is generated at startup (tokens will be
# invalidated on restart)
# Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
# SOLIPLEX_URL_SAFE_TOKEN_SECRET=your-secret-token-here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Session middleware token
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Token for managing session state.
# If not set, a random value is generated at startup (tokens will be
# invalidated on restart)
# Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
# SOLIPLEX_SESSION_MIDDLEWARE_TOKEN=your-secret-token-here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logfire
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Your Logfire API key (required to do logging to Logfire
# Get from: https://logfire.pydantic.dev/login
# LOGFIRE_TOKEN=pylf...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OpenAI
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Your OpenAI API key (required only if one or more agents are configured
# to use Google Gemini).
# Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gemini (if using Gemini LLM provider)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Your Gemini API key (required only if one or more agents are configured
# to use Google Gemini).
# Get from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Smithery.AI MCP Tool Registry
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required only if using MCP tools from Smithery.AI registry
# Used in example/rooms/mcptest configuration
# Get from: https://smithery.ai/
# SMITHERY_AI_API_KEY=your-smithery-api-key
# SMITHERY_AI_PROFILE=your-profile-name

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Maps API
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required only if using Google Maps tools in MCP configurations
# Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=AIzaSy...

# =============================================================================
# Notes
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Security: Never commit .env file to version control
#    Add .env to .gitignore
#
# 2. Docker: When using docker-compose, this file can be loaded automatically
#    via the env_file directive in docker-compose.yaml
#
# 3. Secret Management: For production, consider:
#    - Docker Secrets
#    - Kubernetes Secrets
#    - AWS Secrets Manager
#    - Azure Key Vault
#    - HashiCorp Vault
#
# 4. Configuration Files: Secrets can also be configured in installation YAML
#    using the secrets: section with various source types
#
# 5. Environment Variable Priority:
#    - Installation YAML configuration (highest priority)
#    - .env file
#    - Explicitly set environment variables
#    - System defaults (lowest priority)
#
# 6. Required vs Optional:
#    - OLLAMA_BASE_URL or OPENAI_API_KEY: Required (choose one)
#    - SOLIPLEX_URL_SAFE_TOKEN_SECRET: Recommended (auto-generated if missing)
#    - SOLIPLEX_SESSION_MIDDLEWARE_TOKEN: Recommended (auto-generated if
#      missing)
#    - All others: Optional (feature-dependent)
#
# =============================================================================
